Rating: 4
I made this for a large crowd, so I cooked it in a large pot instead of a skillet. I used lots of garlic, red onions, carrots, celery, tons of zucchini and fresh oregano. Cooked this all very slowly, allowing the vegetables to get pretty "mushy." I used a can of the diced tomatoes and used just about all of the juice in there. Stacked the tilapia over the top, and just let it all cook. I served this with a warm baby red potato salad with red onions and a dijon vinagrette. The next day, those leftover vegetables were awesome with the leftover potatoes. I know that they say that you can't please all of the people, but I definitely did with this recipe. Very Mediterranean and really fantastic with a light white wine. I will make this on a regular basis for the rest of my life.

